A Magistrate’s Court sitting in Abakaliki, Ebonyi State yesterday sentenced a lady, Uzoamaka Aleke, to four years imprisonment with hard labour for stealing two children. The suspect stole two children, Thadius Nwonu (four) and Chinaza Nwonu (five).  The children, a boy and a girl, were said to be siblings. They were stolen by the suspect at Iga-Ishieke community in the Ebonyi Local Government Area of the state on April 7, 2019.  She was arraigned before the Magistrate’s Court, sitting in Abakaliki on a two-count charge bordering on child stealing and conspiracy.  The police prosecutor, Eze Mathias, told the court that the offences were punishable under Section 516A(a) of the Criminal Code Cap. 33, Vol. 1, Laws of Ebonyi State of Nigeria, 2009 and Section 33(1) 3 of Ebonyi State Child Rights and Related Matters Law, 2010.  The charge reads: “That you, Uzoamaka Aleke ‘f’ and others now at large on the 7th day of April, 2019, at Iga Ishieke, Ebonyi Local Government Area of the state, within the jurisdiction of this Honourable Court, did conspire among yourselves to commit felony to wit, child stealing and thereby committed an offence punishable under Section 516A(a) of the Criminal Code Cap. 33, Vol. 1, Laws of Ebonyi State of Nigeria, 2009.  “That you, Uzoamaka Aleke ‘f,’ and others now at large on the same date, time and place in the aforesaid Magisterial District did unlawfully steal one Thadius Nwonu ‘m’, aged four years and Chinaza Nwonu ‘f’, aged five years, without the consent of their parents and thereby committed an offence punishable under Section 33(1) contrary to Section (3) of Ebonyi State Child Rights and Related Matters Law, 2010.”  The Chief Magistrate, Nnenna Onuoha, said the suspect committed grievous offence against humanity and sentenced her to four years imprisonment, with hard labour, without an option of fine.